        "subject": "LU-6612 obdfilter: more debug upon filter_find_olg() failure",
        "message": "LU-6612 obdfilter: more debug upon filter_find_olg() failure\n\nThis patch adds more debug info to track filter_find_olg() failures\nsuspected to cause LLOG unlink/setattr records to be leaked.\n\nThis may come from a flaw in unlink/setattr where Clients may send\ncookies provided by MDT to OSTs when MDS has been disconnected from\nOSS. This will cause FID_SEQ_OST_MDT0 group to be unavailable on\nOSS side and then prevent llog_cancel() to be called by OSS in\norder to cancel and remove LLOG record cookies recorded on MDS.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly envdefinitions=PTLDEBUG=-1\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I691eaf8dbdf2932c5ef14a955a9d23bf3ca0e2da\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
